
[1]guise

   GUISE, n. gize.

   1. External appearance; dress; garb. He appeared in the guise of a
   shepherd. The hypocrite wears the guise of religion.

   That love which is without dissimulation, wears not the guise of modern
   liberality.

   2. Manner; mien; cast of behavior.

   By their guise

   Just men they seem.

   3. Custom; mode; practice.

   The swain replied, it never was our guise,

   To slight the poor, or aught humane despise.
